Name: MINIMUM HORIZONTAL CURVE RADIUS IN METRES
RADIUS IN NAUTICAL MILES
Explanation: THE RADIUS IN NAUTICAL MILES OF A CIRCLE, CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME.

Name: FRONT RADIUS IN METRES
Explanation: THE RADIUS IN METRES OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME EXTENDING FROM THE FRONT SIDE OF A VEHICLE OR OTHER OBJECT.

Name: REAR RADIUS IN METRES
Explanation: THE RADIUS IN METRES OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME EXTENDING FROM THE REAR SIDE OF A VEHICLE OR OTHER OBJECT.

Explanation: THE RADIUS IN METRES OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME EXTENDING FROM THE STARBOARD OR RIGHT-HAND SIDE OF A VEHICLE OR OTHER OBJECT.

Name: PORT RADIUS IN METRES
Explanation: THE RADIUS IN METRES OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME EXTENDING FROM THE PORT OR LEFT-HAND SIDE OF A VEHICLE OR OTHER OBJECT.

Name: BOTTOM RADIUS IN METRES
Explanation: THE RADIUS IN METRES OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME EXTENDING FROM THE BOTTOM SIDE OF A VEHICLE OR OTHER OBJECT.

Name: TOP RADIUS IN METRES
Explanation: THE RADIUS IN METRES OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME EXTENDING FROM THE TOP SIDE OF A VEHICLE OR OTHER OBJECT.

Name: RADIUS IN METRES, 1-99999
Explanation: THE RADIUS OF A CIRCULAR AREA OR SPHERICAL VOLUME MEASURED IN METRES, FROM 1 THROUGH 99999.

Name: RADIUS OF INNER ANNULUS IN NAUTICAL MILES
Explanation: THE RADIUS OF THE INNER ANNULUS IN NAUTICAL MILES
